730
00:39:34.664 --> 00:39:37.083
- Rome is an
irresistible target.

731
00:39:37.083 --> 00:39:39.878
Nothing screams we
are making progress

732
00:39:39.878 --> 00:39:41.296
than to have captured Rome.

733
00:39:41.546 --> 00:39:44.716
And Mark Clark fundamentally
thinks that the Fifth Army.

734
00:39:44.716 --> 00:39:47.677
who has slogged their way
up the Italian peninsula.

735
00:39:47.677 --> 00:39:50.722
and him in particular.
should get credit for this.

736
00:39:53.683 --> 00:39:55.560
- The conquest of
Rome is to take out

737
00:39:55.560 --> 00:39:57.520
one of the great
Axis capitals

738
00:39:57.520 --> 00:39:58.354
in the war.

739
00:39:58.354 --> 00:39:59.522
And what you're doing

740
00:39:59.522 --> 00:40:01.190
is pointing out to
the rest of the world

741
00:40:01.190 --> 00:40:03.151
that we're on the
march. it's happening.

742
00:40:03.151 --> 00:40:05.403
and next stop. Berlin.

743
00:40:08.281 --> 00:40:12.201
- The first of the Axis
capitals is now in our hands.

744
00:40:13.703 --> 00:40:15.246
One up

745
00:40:15.246 --> 00:40:17.624
and two
to go.

746
00:40:17.624 --> 00:40:19.834
- However. the
liberation of Rome

747
00:40:19.834 --> 00:40:23.004
is gonna be entirely
overshadowed

748
00:40:23.004 --> 00:40:27.133
because the next day is going
to be the launch of D-Day.

749
00:40:27.133 --> 00:40:30.595
and Roosevelt can't
say anything about it.

750
00:40:32.680 --> 00:40:33.932
- After 10 months.

751
00:40:34.057 --> 00:40:36.601
the Allies have reached
the Italian capital.

752
00:40:37.894 --> 00:40:40.688
But General Clark's
decision to take Rome

753
00:40:40.688 --> 00:40:43.358
allows the Germans
to escape once again.

754
00:40:44.484 --> 00:40:46.361
- Ever since. he's had
to answer questions

755
00:40:46.361 --> 00:40:48.196
about those orders.

756
00:40:48.196 --> 00:40:51.074
Was his ego simply too
large to pass up Rome?

757
00:40:52.283 --> 00:40:54.202
- Ultimately.
the liberation of Rome

758
00:40:54.202 --> 00:40:57.246
has more symbolic
than strategic value.

759
00:40:58.164 --> 00:41:01.000
The Allies would continue to
fight the Germans in Italy

760
00:41:01.000 --> 00:41:02.961
for almost another year.

761
00:41:04.587 --> 00:41:05.880
- I think Churchill
went to his grave thinking

762
00:41:05.880 --> 00:41:07.966
there was an opportunity
there that was missed.

763
00:41:07.966 --> 00:41:12.595
Churchill always believed
that it had been a good idea.

764
00:41:12.595 --> 00:41:16.224
but it had been undone
by a bit of foot dragging

765
00:41:16.224 --> 00:41:17.600
and some bad luck.

766
00:41:19.602 --> 00:41:22.397
- The Italian
campaign is the moment

767
00:41:22.397 --> 00:41:25.441
at which Churchill
overreaches himself.

768
00:41:25.441 --> 00:41:29.070
He had insisted on this
vast continental campaign

769
00:41:29.070 --> 00:41:31.280
that had led to
nothing but misery.

770
00:41:33.449 --> 00:41:35.493
- Because
of difficult terrain.

771
00:41:35.493 --> 00:41:37.996
military miscalculation.

772
00:41:37.996 --> 00:41:42.000
and determined resistance
from a skillful enemy.

773
00:41:42.000 --> 00:41:46.754
the Allied effort in Italy
gained little and cost much.

774
00:41:47.797 --> 00:41:49.882
- The Italian campaign
is the last time

775
00:41:49.882 --> 00:41:53.761
the British will have
a predominant presence

776
00:41:53.761 --> 00:41:55.847
in the Allied forces.

777
00:41:55.847 --> 00:41:59.642
America has been building
airplanes and tanks.

778
00:41:59.642 --> 00:42:01.561
and creating soldiers.

779
00:42:01.561 --> 00:42:04.564
As the American strength rises.

780
00:42:04.564 --> 00:42:07.316
Winston Churchill's
influence wanes.

781
00:42:10.278 --> 00:42:11.404
- The battle for Italy.

782
00:42:11.571 --> 00:42:13.322
which will go on until
the end of the war.

783
00:42:13.322 --> 00:42:16.242
was fought with
determination and bravery.

784
00:42:16.242 --> 00:42:18.202
Ordinary soldiers
fought for their nation.

785
00:42:18.202 --> 00:42:20.913
but also for each other.

786
00:42:20.913 --> 00:42:22.874
This kind of comradery is found

787
00:42:22.874 --> 00:42:26.002
in all theaters and
on all battlefields.

788
00:42:26.002 --> 00:42:28.212
War tests the best of us.

789
00:42:28.212 --> 00:42:31.674
And nowhere would
men be tested more

790
00:42:31.674 --> 00:42:33.801
than in the skies over Germany.

790
